## 8. The TechInnovate example — what it teaches

The paragraph uses **TechInnovate**, a multinational company, as an example of what happens when project work lacks PMO coordination. Different teams use different methods, causing inconsistency, delays, and cost overruns. The PMO is introduced to restore control, align effort, and improve delivery performance. 

### The lesson behind the scenario

| Problem                     | PMO response                                | Result                |
| --------------------------- | ------------------------------------------- | --------------------- |
| Different methodologies     | Standardization                             | More consistency      |
| Delays and overruns         | Governance + monitoring                     | Better predictability |
| Weak connection to strategy | Prioritization and leadership collaboration | Better focus          |
| Delivery friction           | Training, support, resources                | Better performance    |

### Memory insight

**The PMO turns fragmented execution into coordinated execution.**

